# tok-sync.conf — token → GitHub Actions secrets mapping (EXAMPLE)
#
# Copy this file to ~/.config/flow/tok-sync.conf (chezmoi-managed so it
# syncs across machines). Override the path with FLOW_TOK_SYNC_CONF.
#
# Format (flat, whitespace-delimited — this file is NEVER sourced):
#   <token-name>  <secret-name>  <owner/repo>  [oidc]
#
# - Blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored.
# - One row per (secret, repo) pair. List a token-name on multiple rows
#   to fan it out to several secrets and/or repos.
# - The optional trailing `oidc` flag marks a row as OIDC-capable: tok
#   NEVER pushes those rows. Instead it prints a note recommending GitHub
#   Trusted Publishing — add `permissions: id-token: write` and use
#   `pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish` so the token secret can be dropped.
#
# Auto-sync runs after a successful `tok github|npm|pypi`, `tok rotate`,
# or `tok <name> --refresh` (lists targets, confirms once [y/N], default N).
# Disable per-call with `--no-sync`, or session-wide with FLOW_TOK_AUTOSYNC=0.
# Manual fan-out: `tok sync push <name>`. Dry inspect: `tok sync repos <name>`.

# <token-name>  <secret-name>     <owner/repo>     [oidc]
github-app       APP_ID            data-wise/flow-cli
github-app       APP_PRIVATE_KEY   data-wise/flow-cli
github-app       APP_ID            data-wise/aiterm
github-app       APP_PRIVATE_KEY   data-wise/aiterm
github-app       APP_ID            data-wise/examark
github-app       APP_PRIVATE_KEY   data-wise/examark
github-app       APP_ID            data-wise/nexus-cli
github-app       APP_PRIVATE_KEY   data-wise/nexus-cli
pypi             PYPI_TOKEN        data-wise/nexus-cli   oidc
